## Product Development Report (PDR)\
\
### Executive Summary\
OogCycle is a simple, cute, and user-friendly period tracking web application designed for personal use. The app will provide essential menstrual cycle tracking functionality through an intuitive calendar interface, focusing on ease of use and aesthetic appeal while maintaining privacy and data security.\
\
### Product Vision\
To create the most delightful and straightforward period tracking experience that helps users understand their menstrual cycles without overwhelming complexity or unnecessary features.\
\
### Target User\
- Primary user: Your girlfriend (and potentially other women seeking simple period tracking)\
- Age range: 18-45\
- Tech comfort level: Basic to intermediate\
- Needs: Simple, private, and reliable cycle tracking\
\
### Core Features & Requirements\
\
#### Essential Features\
- **Calendar Interface**: Clean, month-view calendar as the primary interface[1][2]\
- **Period Tracking**: Easy logging of menstrual period start/end dates[1][2]\
- **Ovulation Tracking**: Automatic prediction and manual adjustment of ovulation dates[1][3]\
- **Mood & Symptoms**: Simple mood tracking with cute icons/emojis[1][4]\
- **Cycle Predictions**: Smart predictions based on historical data[1][2]\
- **Data Privacy**: Local storage with optional backup functionality[2][5]\
\
#### Nice-to-Have Features\
- **Cute Themes**: Soft, pastel color schemes with adorable illustrations\
- **Gentle Reminders**: Optional notifications for upcoming periods\
- **Notes Feature**: Daily diary entries for additional context[6]\
- **Cycle Statistics**: Basic cycle length and pattern insights[2]\
\
### Technical Specifications\
- **Platform**: Progressive Web App (PWA) for mobile-first experience\
- **Hosting**: GitHub Pages (static hosting)\
- **Technology Stack**: HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript (vanilla or lightweight framework)\
- **Data Storage**: Local Storage API with JSON export capability\
- **Offline Support**: Full functionality without internet connection[6]\
\
### User Experience Design Principles\
\
#### Simplicity First\
- Minimal learning curve - intuitive interface that requires no tutorials[6]\
- One-tap period logging directly from calendar view[2][6]\
- Clean, uncluttered design with focus on essential information[1]\
\
#### Cute & Approachable\
- Soft color palette (pastels, warm tones)\
- Friendly iconography and illustrations\
- Delightful micro-interactions and animations\
- Welcoming, non-clinical language\
\
#### Privacy & Security\
- All data stored locally on device[2][5]\
- No account creation required[7]\
- Optional PIN protection for sensitive data[2][5]\
- Clear data export/import functionality\
\
### Success Metrics\
- **Ease of Use**: User can log period within 30 seconds of opening app\
- **Accuracy**: Predictions improve with each cycle logged\
- **Engagement**: Regular daily/weekly usage for tracking\
- **Satisfaction**: Positive feedback on design and functionality\
